Default HTML parameters consist of `$content`, `$attr` and `$dent`.

~~~ .php.xmp
HTML::{$any}(string $content = "", array $attr = [], $dent = 0);
~~~

**Example:**

~~~ .php
echo HTML::div('Content goes hereâ€¦', [
    'id' => 'main',
    'class' => 'main'
]);
~~~

**Result:**

~~~ .html
<div class="main" id="main"></div>
~~~

If `$content` value is `false`, then the result will become a self-closed HTML tag.

**Example:**

~~~ .php
echo HTML::input(false, [
    'name' => 'author'
    'type' => 'text'
]);
~~~

**Result:**

~~~ .html
<input name="author" type="text">
~~~